%% D04 · Caucus — bounded peer visibility
%% Answers: When peer visibility is granted, how is it scoped?
%% Referenced in §07 Communication Topology.

flowchart TB
    CSO["Cohort Sub-Orchestrator<br/>(spawns caucus with budget)"]

    subgraph Caucus["Caucus · bounded scope"]
        direction TB
        note1["Scope: N &le; 4 experts<br/>Turns: &le; 6 each<br/>Tokens: &le; 20K total<br/>Wall-clock: &le; 10 min"]
        subgraph Peers["Peer-visible during caucus only"]
            P1["Expert A<br/>(proposer)"]
            P2["Expert B<br/>(critic)"]
            P3["Adversary<br/>(debate)"]
            J["Judge / Arbitrator<br/>(LLM-as-Judge)"]
        end
        note1 -.- Peers
        P1 <--> P2
        P2 <--> P3
        P1 <--> P3
        P1 --> J
        P2 --> J
        P3 --> J
    end

    SUM["Transcript summarized<br/>at cohort boundary<br/>(packet only carries summary)"]
    CSO --> Caucus
    J --> SUM
    SUM --> CSO

    classDef csoCls fill:#ede4d3,stroke:#7a6545,color:#2d2317
    classDef noteCls fill:#f5e6d3,stroke:#8b5a2b,color:#3a2817,stroke-dasharray: 4 2
    classDef peerCls fill:#f7f0e3,stroke:#8a7555,color:#2d2317
    classDef judgeCls fill:#e8dccc,stroke:#5a4a3a,color:#2d2317
    classDef sumCls fill:#fbe7d4,stroke:#c66b2a,color:#3a2817

    class CSO csoCls
    class note1 noteCls
    class P1,P2,P3 peerCls
    class J judgeCls
    class SUM sumCls
